Package de.must.markup

Markup user interface components like HTML creating components with database connection.

          Description

Interface Summary
Invokable Invokables are components to be invoked by SessionStd and put in stack to control state maintaining and back functionality.
Markupable A view to different types of objects to be rendered via markup language.
Presentable A view to different types of presentable components, whose values shall be loaded.
SessionDataAddOn Interface to plug in individual session attributes to make it available wherever SessionData is available.
Storable A view to different types of markupable components, whose values shall be loaded and stored.

Package de.must.markup Description

Markup user interface components like HTML creating components with database connection. Numerious data components (Storable) are available to be laid-out in special frame-like container for querying and administrating database tables. A similar developing toolkit for Swing UI is available with package de.must.wuic

Concept: Think in java objects and let the framework generate what you need, e.g. HTML. If Java Server Pages are wished, you may also benefit from the package markup by using e.g. GroupOfStorables
